  "local_port": 33048,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What should I do to get selected in GSOC 2018?",
  "response": "Getting selected for Google Summer of Code (GSoC) can be competitive, but with the right approach, you can improve your chances significantly. Here are some steps you should follow, specifically for GSoC 2018 or any other year, as the process is often similar:\n\n1. **Understand GSoC**: Familiarize yourself with the GSoC program, its timeline, and requirements. Review the official GSoC website for essential guidelines.\n\n2. **Choose a Suitable Organization**: Browse through the list of participating organizations. Look for organizations that align with your interests and expertise. Check their project ideas and see where you can contribute.\n\n3. **Get Involved Early**: Engage with the organization before the application period starts:\n   - Join their mailing lists or forums.\n   - Participate in their discussions and ask questions.\n   - Start contributing to their projects on platforms like GitHub or GitLab.\n\n4. **Pick a Project Idea**: Choose a project idea that you find exciting and that matches your skills. If there aren\u2019t any project ideas that suit you, consider proposing your own.\n\n5. **Make Contributions**: Aim to make meaningful contributions to the organization\u2019s codebase. This could involve fixing bugs, improving documentation, or adding features. This will demonstrate your commitment and help you get noticed.\n\n6. **Communicate Effectively**: Good communication skills are essential. Be clear and concise in your interactions. Ask for feedback on your contributions and be open to suggestions.\n\n7. **Submit a Strong Proposal**: When the application period opens, write a detailed and clear proposal. Include:\n   - Your understanding of the project.\n   - A timeline of deliverables (a breakdown of what you plan to achieve weekly).\n   - Your schedule and availability.\n   - Information on your previous contributions.\n   - Any references, if applicable.\n\n8. **Seek Feedback on Your Proposal**: Before submitting, get feedback from mentors or other community members within the organization. They can provide valuable insights and help you improve your proposal.\n\n9. **Prepare for Interviews**: Sometimes organizations may have an interview process. Be ready to discuss your proposal, your contributions, and your ideas in-depth.\n\n10. **Stay Engaged**: Throughout the application process, remain active in the community. Keep contributing and communicating with the organization.\n\n11. **Follow the Timeline**: Adhere to deadlines and ensure that you manage your time wisely. Check the GSoC site for the timeline of events and make sure you don\u2019t miss any crucial dates.\n\n12. **Be Persistent**: If you don\u2019t get accepted this year, learn from the experience, seek feedback, and consider reapplying in the future.\n\nFollowing these steps can help improve your chances of being selected for GSoC. Good luck!",
